# A comment body containing `--!>` (HTML5 comment-end-bang close) is REJECTED — it
# survives the parser (only `-->` stops it) but would break out of the comment in a
# browser, turning following source into live markup. Rejected, not silently emitted.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component C() {
	<div><!-- ok --!> <script>alert(1)</script> --></div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:7: HTML comment text contains a comment-close sequence (`-->` or `--!>`); it would break out of the comment
